  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Computer Vision Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Develop vision and 3D perception algorithms using deep learning and geometric methods.</li><li>Work with point clouds, depth data, and multimodal fusion (camera + LiDAR).</li><li>Build and maintain calibration pipelines (camera, LiDAR, IMU).</li><li>Implement production-quality code in C++ and Python.</li><li>Optimize models for real-time or embedded platforms      (quantization, pruning, GPU tuning).</li><li>Deploy and maintain inference pipelines for cloud or edge devices.</li><li>Collaborate across teams to integrate perception into production systems.</li></ul><p><strong>Required Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Strong background in computer vision, deep learning, or 3D perception.</li><li>Experience with CNNs, transformers, and point cloud/3D vision methods (stereo, depth, SLAM).</li><li>Proficiency in Python and C++ for algorithm and system development.</li><li>Hands-on calibration experience (intrinsic/extrinsic, LiDAR-camera, IMU).</li><li>Experience with PyTorch or TensorFlow.</li><li>Model optimization and deployment on GPUs or embedded devices (Jetson, ARM, accelerators).</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Master’s or PhD in Computer Vision, Robotics, ML, or related fields.</li><li>Experience with sensor fusion frameworks and spatial AI systems.</li><li>Background in robotics, mapping, or edge perception systems.</li><li>Familiarity with MLOps or large-scale deployment workflows.</li></ul><p><strong>What We Offer</strong></p><ul><li>Opportunities to work on advanced 2D/3D perception and multimodal AI.</li><li>Ownership of production-grade, real-time vision systems.</li><li>A collaborative engineering and research‑driven environment.</li><li>Competitive compensation and technical growth opportunities.</li></ul>",
